About 50 Sanderlings vocalizing as they moved along the beach en masse; for Sanderlings, this was a bit unusual as they were not chasing the waves but were instead on hard-packed smooth sand (the "beach face").  Time was at 8:25 AM, with the previous low tide at 5:24 AM and the next high tide at 11:41 AM.
Calls as the bird flies away after it walked up to me on the beach.
